      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "content": "## SFlowG OTLP Overview\nThis dashboard is provisioned for the ecommerce example and covers every OTLP signal the framework currently emits here.\n\n### Metrics shown here\n- Flow counters and latency histograms\n- Step counters, latency histograms, and retries\n- Plugin call counters and latency histograms\n- HTTP request counters and latency histograms\n- User/business metrics (orders created, payment attempts)\n\n### Logs\nLogs are exported through `observability.logging.export` to Loki. The logs panel below defaults to `service_name=\"ecommerce-api\"`, and logs preserve runtime correlation fields such as `trace_id`, `span_id`, `execution_id`, and `flow_id`.\n\n### Traces\nTracing is enabled for this example and exported to Tempo through the bundled collector.\n\nOpen **Explore**, select the **Tempo** datasource, and start with queries like:\n- `{ resource.service.name = \"ecommerce-api\" }`\n- `{ name = \"flow create_order\" }`\n- `{ name = \"step pay_order\" }`\n- `{ name = \"plugin http.request\" }`\n\nSpan names follow the framework runtime model:\n- `flow <flow-id>`\n- `step <step-id>`\n- `plugin <plugin-name>.<method>`",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "12.0.0",
      "title": "Overview",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": "Loki",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 10,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 59
      },
      "id": 14,
      "options": {
        "dedupStrategy": "none",
        "enableLogDetails": true,
        "prettifyLogMessage": false,
        "showCommonLabels": false,
        "showLabels": true,
        "showTime": true,
        "sortOrder": "Descending",
        "wrapLogMessage": true
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "editorMode": "code",
          "expr": "{service_name=\"ecommerce-api\"}",
          "queryType": "range",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Application Logs",
      "type": "logs"
    },
